Smart Attributes - 20 April 1998

Smart Attributes provide a consistent means of extracting information from an object by adding
a prefix to the attribute's name.  In general, they can be used anywhere a regular attribute
can be used.

Available Prefixes
SA_DYN	Extract from dynamic tables
SA_TBL	Extract from any table or view (with assembly_cat,nam,ver,seqno defined).
SA_SET  Extract from a set of attributes
SA_AST  Extract from attached assembly tree
SA_PPL  Execute a ppl
SA_EXP  Execute an expression
SA_PDM  Misc pdm information
SA_OBJ  Misc object information

Examples:
SA_DYN:volume			
	Same as dyn_select("volume") function, volume is pulled from database,
	any other posted attribute can be used, transient caching makes this faster
	than dyn_select, cache is cleared each time a file is retrieved

SA_TBL:my_table:my_attr
	Pulls my_attr from any database table named "my_table"
	Useful when database table views have been created by the database administrator

SA_SET:Production:pri_process	
	Pulls primary process from the production data.
	Note that 'Production' is the set type, any customer defined set type can be used.
        This prefix hides the mapping of a set type to it's dynamic table

SA_AST:AssyTree:PSU:node_name 
	Pulls node_name from an assembly tree from the psu to which the piece belongs to
	Any attribute can be used in place of node_name
        
SA_AST:AssyTree:1:an_attr
	Pulls an_attr from an assembly tree from the first parent stage the piece belongs to
	Use 2,3,4 to go up the tree as desired
	Useful for unit drawings where piece representation is based on where the part
	is attached in the assembly tree.

SA_PPL:file_name	
SA_PPL:file_name:function_name:ppl_argument 	
	Executes the ppl function with the piece as input, (defaults to main() functon)
	See $VDS/api/smart_attr/VDsaAttr.u for sample ppl

SA_EXP:exp_name
	Executes the predefined expression 

SA_PME:	(To be defined)
SA_OLE:	(To be defined)

SA_PDM:assembly_cat	 -- PDM information
SA_PDM:assembly_nam
SA_PDM:assembly_ver
SA_PDM:seqno
SA_PDM:post_id		-- Combination of catalog,name,ver and seqno
SA_PDM:file_name
SA_PDM:family		-- PDM catalog which defines part
SA_PDM:dyn_table	-- Default dynamic table

SA_OBJ: category	-- plate,beam,equipment etc. as defined in expression parser
SA_OBJ: class		-- VSplate,VSsubBeam, actual isdp class name
SA_OBJ: objid		-- Unique (within file) object identifier
SA_OBJ: name		-- Name
SA_OBJ: path		-- Full path name
SA_OBJ: layer		-- Symbology information
SA_OBJ: color		
SA_OBJ: weight		
SA_OBJ: style		
SA_OBJ: macro_name	-- Underlying macro name


Note:
A new command "Review Smart Attributes" allows testing these attributes 
by selecting an object and typing in an attribute name.  

